message.content:
A Junonia hierta is a butterfly species found in Asia and parts of Oceania.
It has a medium-sized wingspan and a distinctive pattern of eyespots on its wings.
The wings are a rich brown color with a black and white pattern, and a slight iridescence in the right light.
The body of the butterfly is mainly black and hairy.
When its wings are opened, it reveals a vibrant blue inner color.
It is often found in tropical forests and gardens, feeding on nectar from flowers.
The Junonia hierta is considered a popular species among butterfly enthusiasts and collectors.
